Continue all precautions from lower Threat Conditions:
0M Ensure that key leaders are familiar with the emergency response, COOP and business resumption plans.
0M Review, update and routinely exercise functional areas of plans.
0M Review and update the recall list for emergency response teams
0M Develop or review Mutual Aid agreements with other facilities and/or with local government for use during emergencies.
0M Ensure local law enforcement and security forces have immediate access to building floor plans.
0M Review physical security precautions to prevent theft, unauthorized entry or destruction of property.
Have you provided for:
0M Employee picture ID badges?
0M Background checks on employees?
0M Access control and locking of high
security areas at all times?
0M All security keys marked with "Do not Duplicate"?
0M Surveillance Cameras?
0M Backup power?
0M An alarm system?
0M Advise employees to report suspicious activity to security personnel.
0M Increase liaison with local law enforcement.
Continue all precautions from lower Threat Conditions: 0M Reduce the number of access points for vehicles and personnel to minimum levels, maintaining flow of traffic.
0M Estimate the threat vulnerability of each critical facility and countermeasures required to protect them.
0M Ensure that each department is familiar with their assigned responsibilities during a disaster as shown in plan and prepared to respond.
0M Review communications plans and ensure the recall procedures are current and accurate.
0M Conduct emergency management training and exercise emergency response plans.
0M Ensure all emergency management and response functions are adequately staffed.
Recruit and train volunteers to augment full time staff.
0M Actively support the Neighborhood Watch, Community Emergency Response Team (CERT), VIPS, MRC and Amateur Radio Emergency Service programs.
0M Remind citizen and employees to be alert for suspicious packages, activities, vehicles and to report these occurrences to the proper authority.
0M Secure buildings, unused rooms, storage areas, equipment and vehicles to prevent theft, tampering or destruction.
0M Evaluate information available on public websites that could compromise security.
0M Encourage all citizens and employees to have necessary immunizations.
