0M Develop emergency response, cooperative agreement (COOP) and business resumption plans.
0M Encourage and assist employees to be prepared for personal, natural and technological emergencies.
0M Develop a communications roster and recall system for emergency response and key personnel.
0M Conduct training for employees on physical security precautions.
0M Budget for and implement heightened physical security measures.
0M Identify critical facilities and key assets that may need protection.
0M Review Emergency Response Plans.
0M Conduct training, seminars, workshops and exercises using the emergency response plans.
0M Conduct emergency preparedness training for citizens and employees.
0M Encourage response agencies (fire fighters, law enforcement, EMS, public works and elected officials) to take emergency management and American Red Cross first aid and CPR training.
0M Actively Support Citizen Corps Program.
0M Provide emergency preparedness information to employees via paycheck stubs tips, newsletters, articles and posters.
0M Conduct routine inventories of emergency supplies and medical aid kits.
0M Budget for physical security measures.
0M Encourage programs for employee immunization and preventive health care.
