0M Continue to enjoy individual freedom.
Participate freely in travel, work and recreational activities.
0M Be prepared for disasters and family emergencies, develop a family emergency plan.
(See Family Emergency Preparedness Guide and American Red Cross brochures.)
0M Know how to turn off your power, gas and water service to your house.
0M Know what hazardous materials are stored in your home and how to and properly dispose of unneeded chemicals.
0M Support the efforts of your local emergency responders (fire fighters, law enforcement and emergency medical service).
0M Know what natural hazards are prevalent in your area and what measures you can take to protect your family.
